    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="533"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d533">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1199.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Livingston</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Cape Haitien</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 21, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Rebels retreated in good order Saturday afternoon preceded by many women and
                    children and will probably continue revolution. Many refugees in consulates and
                    some aboard French cruiser. Detachments <pb facs="0589" n="473" xml:id="pg_473"
                    /> of marines are guarding French Consulate, bank and bishopric. There were some
                    executions yesterday for pillaging.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Livingston</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
